args:
Renee's weakness is an inability to work in
harmony with her sisters, which stems from an
inferiority complex over her lack of a special
ability. But once she learns of her power to cool
objects with magic, her confidence returns. The
group then enters the final task of the training.
After night fell in the midst of Renee's training,\nthe party gathered ingredients for dinner.
Meat, fish, fruits, and veggies...\nThis is quite the feast we've assembled.
Eatin' in the woods like this\nmakes it feel like a camp-out.
...No, I can't get into that mindset.\nWe're trainin' here, not havin' fun!
Oh, I think it's all right for us\nto let our hair down a LITTLE.
Right! Let's put cares aside for a while\nand just enjoy the bounty of the forest.
We have a lot of different things in this\nmakeshift buffet, but it seems like they're\nall going to complement each other nicely.
I guess there's a certain harmony\nto everything in the forest, huh?

Coach! Remember all that stuff you were
saying about cooperating and whatever?
Is THAT why I'm here? So I can learn
harmony from the forest?
BOOOOM GOES THE DYNAMITE!\nYessir, the lives of the forest all support\neach other, and you gotta do the same.

But there must have been a way to make
that point without dragging everybody
out into the woods! I mean, back me
up here, Ramona! You too, Rena!
Hmm... How should I put this...?
Well, I think Coach is right: You DO need\nto be more in harmony with the two of us.
Nooooo! Is my work REALLY that bad?!
That ain't what I'm sayin'! We both know\nhow hard you work, and we appreciate it.
But sometimes you just work...TOO hard.
At times, Renee, you get so wrapped up\nin your own enthusiasm that you end\nup spinning your wheels a little.
Remember earlier when you were about\nto run off into the woods without a torch?
Aw, I just got excited, is all!
But that excitement made you careless.\nAnd honestly, we've both seen the same\nthing happen in your smithing.
I know you wanna be the best smith ever,\nbut if you try to race to that goal without\nsome kinda plan, you'll never get there.
Is my dream of becoming the greatest\nblacksmith ever REALLY that hopeless?!
Neither of you understand me at aaaaall!
It's soooo unfair! You both got an ability\nfrom Dad, and I didn't get ANYTHING!
Why, so you can make fun of your dumb\nlittle sister and her dumb no-skills?!\nAaaargh! It's soooo humiliating!
Renee, that's not what we're saying.\nPerhaps you really haven't realized?
You DO have one of Dad's powers.
Nuh-uh! I just have the power of\na stupid shop lackey!
＂Go here, Renee!＂ ＂Clean this up, Renee!＂\n＂Cool this metal down, Renee!＂
Well, you see, Renee, cooling things IS\nyour power!
Yeah, right. I just throw a big bucket of\nwater on hot metal—any idiot can do that.
No, think about it. We use fire infused with\nmana to temper our weapons, right?
That ain't no ordinary kind of heat,\nwhich means it ain't just any kind\nof water that can cool it down!
You're not just throwing buckets of water\non hot steel, Sis—you're cooling it down\nwith YOUR POWER.
I wouldn't lie to you about that.
Honestly, it's pretty damn impressive\nyou've been using it this whole time\nwithout even realizin' it.
Hee hee! Oh man, that is CLASSIC me.

If I was able to do the work I did without
even being aware of my power, then I
oughta be able to do even MORE amazing
work now that I know I've got it!
From now on, I'm gonna chill\nthat metal down ICE-COLD!
*sigh* Did we not JUST discuss\nyou not getting carried away?
If you cool a weapon down too quickly,\nit's likely to develop cracks.
Wait, it IS?! I mean, uh...I knew that.
It's just like Coach has been saying—\nthe most important thing is harmony!
Yessir, that's the ticket! If you all work\nas part of a well-oiled machine, there\nain't nothing that can stop ya!
If you take nothing else from this part of\nthe program, remember these words...
It's all for one and one for all,\nand there's no I in team!
Now it's on to the next stage of\nthe program...FIEND SLAYING!
I don't really understand it either,\nbut I'm sure it will make sense in time.
We just gotta believe in Coach!
Sounds like you've got a fight brewing,\nso we'll lend a hand. C'mon, everyone!
